# React Frontend Rules

## Components
- Function components only — no class components, ever.
- One component per file. Default-export the component, named-export anything else.
- Folder per component: `src/components/Button/{Button.tsx, Button.css, Button.test.tsx}`.
- Props typed with an interface named `<Component>Props`. Place it directly above the component.
- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow.

## Hooks
- All hooks at the top of the component, in fixed order. No conditional hooks.
- Custom hooks live in `src/hooks/` and start with `use`.
- Side effects go in `useEffect` with an exhaustive dependency array — never disable `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`.

## State
- Local state first. Lift only when shared.
- No prop drilling beyond 2 levels — use context or a custom hook.
- For server state (Supabase queries), use a single fetching pattern across the app. Pick one and stick to it (TanStack Query is the default if asked).

## Supabase access from the frontend
- Always import the client from `src/lib/supabase.ts`. Never call `createClient()` anywhere else.
- Auth state comes from one `useAuth` hook only.
- Never use the service-role key in frontend code. If a task seems to require it, **stop and ask** — it belongs in an Edge Function.

## Files to ask before touching
- `src/main.tsx`, `src/App.tsx`, `src/lib/supabase.ts` — these are foundational. Propose changes before editing.

## Forbidden
- Inline styles (`style={{...}}`) for anything beyond one-off dynamic values.
- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without an explicit security justification.
- `any`, `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error` without a comment explaining why.
